  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PEOPLE EU Volunteers programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is for the CAFOD managed activities related to the EUAV PEOPLE programme. The main activities are CAFOD run workshops (inception, ToTs, mid-term review and closure) and consultancies (CHS training, evaluation and audit).

The aim of the PEOPLE programme is to strengthen the capacity of ten participating organisations in Sierra Leone, Liberia, Nigeria and Zimbabwe to prepare for and respond to humanitarian crises and strengthen their network and volunteer management systems. It is a 2 year consortium project led by CAFOD with Secours Catholique, CRS, Caritas Africa, and 9 other African Caritas partners. The objectives are to:
1. Strengthen humanitarian preparedness and response capacity of 10 local and national organisations to design and deliver needs based humanitarian aid.
2. Strengthen volunteer management capacity of 10 prospective hosting organisations to facilitate integration and active participation of volunteers in humanitarian action.
3. Strengthen collective dialogue, knowledge sharing, learning and peer- to-peer support between partners on volunteers.</narrative>
  </description>
